solution:
The number of $1\times1$ squares in the diagram is $2(n-1)$, the number of $2\times 2$ squares is $n-2$, and the number of $\sqrt{2} \times \sqrt{2}$ squares is also $n-2$ (see diagram).  Solving \[
2(n-1)+n-2+n-2=70
\] we find $n=\boxed{19}$.

